Build succeeds with 0 warnings, 0 errors. Here's the complete summary of all **6 breaking changes** and their fixes:

---

### Fixes applied to this project

| # | Breaking Change | File | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | TFM & packages must target 9.0 | `EfApp.csproj` | `net8.0`→`net9.0`, packages→`9.0.0` |
| 2 | `DateTime.UtcNow` in `HasData` causes "pending model changes" exception | `AppDbContext.cs` | Replaced with fixed constant `new DateTime(2024,1,1,0,0,0,DateTimeKind.Utc)` |
| 3 | `Migrate()` inside explicit transaction now throws | `MigrationRunner.cs` | Removed wrapping `ExecutionStrategy`+`BeginTransaction`; EF Core 9 manages its own |
| 4 | EF Design package not found with SDK 9.0.200+ | `EfApp.csproj` | Added `<Publish>true</Publish>` and `<IncludeAssets>` |

### Fixes needed in your Cosmos DB project

| # | Breaking Change | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| 5 | Discriminator property renamed from `"Discriminator"` to `"$type"` and `id` format changed | In `OnModelCreating`, add for each entity: |

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<YourEntity>()
    .HasDiscriminator<string>("Discriminator");   // keep old property name
modelBuilder.Entity<YourEntity>()
    .HasRootDiscriminatorInJsonId(true);           // keep old compound id format
```

| 6 | Synchronous Cosmos DB I/O now throws | Replace all sync calls with async equivalents: |

```csharp
// BREAKS:  db.SaveChanges();       → db.SaveChangesAsync();
// BREAKS:  query.ToList();         → await query.ToListAsync();
// BREAKS:  query.First();          → await query.FirstAsync();
// BREAKS:  query.Single();         → await query.SingleAsync();
// BREAKS:  query.Count();          → await query.CountAsync();
```
